  </div>
</div>

<div class="case-study">
  <blockquote>
    <p>It&rsquo;s my job to build meaningful communities around products. The ScraperWiki People Pack helps me do that, quickly and efficiently.</p>
    <p>Most recently, I fed names from the <strong>Eventbrite Attendee scraper</strong> into the <strong>LinkedIn Group tool</strong>, to find out the key hotspots where my target community hangs out online.</p>
  </blockquote>
  <div class="person media">
    <img src="https://media.scraperwiki.com/images/about_zach.png" width="42" height="42" class="pull-left">
    <div class="media-body">
      <h4 class="media-heading">Zach Beauvais</h4>
      <p>Community Manager</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="case-study last">
  <blockquote>
    <p>ScraperWiki, and the People Pack, are invaluable tools in my B2B business development workflow.</p>
    <p>I use the <strong>LinkedIn Company tool</strong> to monitor the employees at target companies. Then, when someone joins or leaves a company, I get <strong>Android Push Notifications</strong> so I can instantly get in touch and keep building the relationship.</p>
  </blockquote>
  <div class="person media">
    <img src="/image/about_aine.png" width="42" height="42" class="pull-left">
    <div class="media-body">
      <h4 class="media-heading">Aine McGuire</h4>
      <p>Chief Marketing Officer</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<span class="clearfix"></span>

